data.name: WA-Full Tour
data.title: Audio Guided Tour
data.description:
Embark on a captivating journey through aviation history with our Full Museum Guided Tour on the Canadian Aviation Museum app. Explore the extensive collection, from aviation pioneers to cutting-edge technology, with engaging narratives and multimedia enhancements. Follow the app's expert guidance to discover the stories behind iconic aircraft, historical milestones, and the brilliant minds shaping Canada's aviation legacy. Enjoy an interactive and informative experience, exploring at your own pace and gaining a deeper understanding of the evolution of flight.

Guided Tour Details

  • The tour guide is fully accessible with Audio Content and transcripts provided immediately after.
  • To access each stop, you can either:
    • Place your phone near the NFC tag and tap the top, or
    • Scan the QR code if NFC is not available.
  • The app also features numbered stops accessible by clicking the magnifying glass icon.
  • Accessibility features include:
    • Screen reader compatibility for Audio Content and transcripts,
    • Built-in QR code scanner activated by clicking the magnifying glass icon.

data.name: WA-Collection Highlights
data.title: Collection Highlights
data.description:
Step back in time as we explore the Cold War, a captivating period of geopolitical tension that unfolded after the end of World War II. From March 12, 1947, to December 25, 1991, the United States and the Soviet Union, along with their allies in the Western Bloc and the Eastern Bloc, were engaged in a complex dance of politics and ideologies. How did this era shape the world of aviation? Join us on this journey through our aviation collection to discover the impact of the Cold War on the skies above.

*Currently being updated and closed for public view.

cover_image.name: WA-Collection-Highlights.jpeg
cover_image.description: A mix of yellow colored planes inside the museum.

data.name: WA-Map
data.title: Map
data.description:
Welcome to our interactive Map Tour, a cutting-edge experience at the Canadian Aviation Museum activated by beacon technology. This innovative journey seamlessly blends technology and exploration, guiding you through distinct exhibitions with precision and ease.

As you navigate the museum, beacons strategically placed throughout will trigger each exhibition. This Map Tour ensures that you won't miss any of the fascinating stories, artifacts, and insights that each exhibition has to offer.

So, buckle up and let the beacons be your guide as you embark on a dynamic exploration of the Canadian Aviation Museum. Each exhibition is a chapter waiting to unfold, offering a unique perspective on the incredible world of aviation. Enjoy the freedom to delve into the details that capture your interest, all while the Map Tour effortlessly directs your journey. Get ready for an unparalleled adventure through the skies of history!
